  1. Quiz - price vs. carat # Create a scatterplot of price vs carat # and omit the top 1% of price and carat # values.
#quantile(diamonds$carat, 0.99)

diamonds.sub <- subset(diamonds, carat < quantile(diamonds$carat, 0.99) | 
                         price < quantile(diamonds$price, 0.99))
ggplot(data=diamonds.sub, aes(x=carat, y=price)) +
  geom_point()

9: Quiz - price vs. volume

diamonds$volume <- diamonds$x * diamonds$y * diamonds$z
ggplot(data = diamonds, aes(x=volume, y=price)) +
  geom_point()

  1. Quiz - Correlations on Subsets
diamonds.corsub <- subset(diamonds, volume > 0 & volume <= 800)
cor.test(diamonds.corsub$price, diamonds.corsub$volume)

  1. Quiz: Mean Price by Clarity # Use the function dplyr package # to create a new data frame containing # info on diamonds by clarity.

Name the data frame diamondsByClarity

The data frame should contain the following

variables in this order.

(1) mean_price

(2) median_price

(3) min_price

(4) max_price

(5) n

library(dplyr)
## Warning: package 'dplyr' was built under R version 3.3.3
## 
## Attaching package: 'dplyr'
## The following objects are masked from 'package:stats':
## 
##     filter, lag
## The following objects are masked from 'package:base':
## 
##     intersect, setdiff, setequal, union
diamondsByClarity <- diamonds %>%
  group_by(clarity) %>%
  summarise(mean_price = mean(price),
            median_price = median(price),
            min_price = min(price),
            max_price = max(price),
            n = n())

  1. Quiz: Bar Charts of Mean Price
library(gridExtra)
## Warning: package 'gridExtra' was built under R version 3.3.3
## 
## Attaching package: 'gridExtra'
## The following object is masked from 'package:dplyr':
## 
##     combine
diamonds_by_clarity <- group_by(diamonds, clarity)
diamonds_mp_by_clarity <- summarise(diamonds_by_clarity, 
                                    mean_price = mean(price))

diamonds_by_color <- group_by(diamonds, color)
diamonds_mp_by_color <- summarise(diamonds_by_color, 
                                  mean_price = mean(price))

d_by_clarity <- ggplot(data=diamonds_mp_by_clarity, aes(x=clarity, y=mean_price)) +
  geom_bar(stat='identity')


d_by_color <- ggplot(data=diamonds_mp_by_color, aes(x=color, y=mean_price)) +
  geom_bar(stat='identity')

grid.arrange(d_by_clarity, d_by_color)

  1. Quiz: Trends in Mean Price

mean price decreases as clarity improves mean price increases as color gets worse
